                    </div>
                    <span>It is difficult to understand for whom this book was written. Perhaps for an Aristotelian who is not familar with limits and Dedekind cuts. An interesting but not terribly useful approach to one of the most basic and most hardily considered conundrums at the heart of mathematics.</span>
                  
              
